WEBVTT

00:07.716 --> 00:08.091
.

00:08.133 --> 00:08.758
<i>[jazzy percussive music]</i>

00:09.718 --> 00:12.012
- [sighs]

00:12.053 --> 00:13.471
<i>* *</i>

00:13.513 --> 00:15.098
Damn.

00:15.140 --> 00:16.891
<i>* *</i>

00:16.933 --> 00:18.852
- Damn right.

00:18.893 --> 00:22.689
<i>* *</i>

00:22.731 --> 00:24.232
Mm.

00:33.074 --> 00:35.035
- The sink's clogged again!

00:35.076 --> 00:36.995
- Plumber is coming tomorrow!

00:37.037 --> 00:38.371
- [groans]

00:38.413 --> 00:40.123
It's like a crime scene
in here.

00:40.165 --> 00:41.291
[siren wailing]

00:41.332 --> 00:43.418
- [grumbling]

00:47.339 --> 00:49.966
- Written word not enough, huh?

00:50.008 --> 00:52.469
You want the full
audio experience?

00:52.510 --> 00:54.971
- I need an actual human being,

00:55.013 --> 00:57.599
or someone is getting strangled
with a plunger.

00:58.975 --> 01:00.185
- We still being sexy?

01:00.226 --> 01:02.562
- Look, I've only got
a few weeks left.

01:02.604 --> 01:05.148
<i>It's time to make this</i>
<i>an in-person thing.</i>

01:05.190 --> 01:06.733
- So let's do it.

01:06.775 --> 01:08.068
<i>Tonight.</i>

01:08.109 --> 01:09.944
- For real, for real?

01:09.986 --> 01:11.905
<i>What about your dad?</i>

01:11.946 --> 01:13.073
- Oh, no, no, no, no.

01:13.114 --> 01:15.116
He's--he's doing great.

01:15.158 --> 01:16.951
He's on his meds.
Model roommate.

01:16.993 --> 01:19.662
So it's time for him to see
a sock on the door knob

01:19.704 --> 01:20.830
and get gone.

01:20.872 --> 01:22.207
<i>For real.</i>

01:22.248 --> 01:26.211
<i>* *</i>

01:26.252 --> 01:29.130
- Oh, I know that smile.

01:29.172 --> 01:30.757
That's the smile of a man
making plans

01:30.799 --> 01:33.802
for the finest
fishing exposition

01:33.843 --> 01:35.345
in the tristate area.

01:35.387 --> 01:36.888
- That's a bunch of old timers

01:36.930 --> 01:39.057
swapping stories
in the back of a bait shop?

01:39.099 --> 01:40.350
- Sure.

01:40.392 --> 01:42.102
If you wanna say
the Javits Convention Center

01:42.143 --> 01:43.937
is a bait shop.

01:43.978 --> 01:45.814
- Oh, looks great, Dad.

01:45.855 --> 01:47.107
Yeah, tell me about it.

01:47.148 --> 01:50.318
- I will not,
'cause you're coming.

01:50.360 --> 01:52.195
- Sounds great, Dad.

01:52.237 --> 01:53.279
- Good.

01:53.321 --> 01:55.490
We'll go after your work.

01:55.532 --> 01:57.450
- Wait, the expo's tonight?

01:57.492 --> 01:58.785
- Is that a problem?

01:58.827 --> 02:05.750
<i>* *</i>

02:08.420 --> 02:11.339
<i>[upbeat piano music]</i>

02:11.381 --> 02:14.592
<i>* *</i>

02:14.634 --> 02:17.387
- Mm.

02:17.429 --> 02:20.140
What did you do that for?

02:20.181 --> 02:21.850
- Just making sure you're real.

02:21.891 --> 02:23.768
- [chuckles]

02:23.810 --> 02:28.023
Only way to know for sure
is to give me a scalp massage.

02:28.064 --> 02:30.316
- Dad's back!
- Hi, everybody.

02:30.358 --> 02:32.318
[laughter]

02:32.360 --> 02:34.863
Hi, guys.
You're darn right, Dad's back.

02:34.904 --> 02:36.406
- Yeah.
- I'm here.

02:36.448 --> 02:41.786
- This morning,
my daughter said that

02:41.828 --> 02:47.375
when I'm tired,
I look like a sad racoon.

02:47.417 --> 02:52.714
So do you think I can trade her

02:52.756 --> 02:55.842
for a new car?

02:55.884 --> 02:59.054
- A very nice new car.

02:59.095 --> 03:00.597
- [laughs]

03:00.638 --> 03:02.557
Good.

03:06.227 --> 03:08.146
- Thank you.

03:08.188 --> 03:10.565
- Where do you get
your motivation?

03:12.942 --> 03:13.985
- Good morning.

03:14.027 --> 03:15.653
I have the clinical
trial prospectus.

03:15.695 --> 03:17.280
- Thank you.

03:17.322 --> 03:22.535
Well, Dana, this is Dr. Wilder.

03:22.577 --> 03:28.750
And Dr. Wilder, this is Dana,
my ASL teacher.

03:54.234 --> 03:56.194
- Oh, yeah.
No, I got that one.

03:56.236 --> 03:58.571
Crystal clear.

03:58.613 --> 04:00.407
<i>- * It's a brand new *</i>

04:00.448 --> 04:01.908
- Please give me
something good.

04:01.950 --> 04:04.244
- And this one's
the quarterly budget template.

04:04.285 --> 04:05.537
- Another? How many are there?

04:05.578 --> 04:07.122
- It's quarterly, so four.

04:07.163 --> 04:08.498
- Sandra Fall, I hate forms.

04:08.540 --> 04:10.000
Forms never helped anyone.

04:10.041 --> 04:12.002
- Well, this one literally
funds the hospital.

04:12.043 --> 04:13.586
- If I'm not looking
into a patient's eyes,

04:13.628 --> 04:16.006
if I'm not looking
into the underlying roots

04:16.047 --> 04:17.716
of their issues, then--

04:17.757 --> 04:19.467
- Then you can do your
actual job, sign these forms,

04:19.509 --> 04:21.261
and end this conversation.
- I had a question.

04:21.302 --> 04:22.721
Is there a form that fires you?

04:22.762 --> 04:24.097
- You keep shredding it
against my wishes.

04:24.139 --> 04:25.473
Sign.

04:27.058 --> 04:28.935
- The ICU needs
a substitute attending?

04:28.977 --> 04:31.021
- Mm-hmm.
Dr. Slavin broke her ankle.

04:31.062 --> 04:32.105
She's out today.

04:32.147 --> 04:34.065
<i>* *</i>

04:34.107 --> 04:38.028
- All right. So today I am not
your boss's boss's boss.

04:38.069 --> 04:39.988
I am just simply your boss.

04:40.030 --> 04:41.698
So I'm here for you.

04:41.740 --> 04:44.826
Let's do some actual medicine.

04:44.868 --> 04:46.953
Who's with me?

04:46.995 --> 04:48.997
- You look chipper.

04:49.039 --> 04:50.331
- Do I?

04:50.373 --> 04:52.042
Well, it is never a bad day
to have a good day,

04:52.083 --> 04:53.209
my enchanting chairwoman.

04:53.251 --> 04:54.836
- Charmed and unnerved.

04:54.878 --> 04:56.463
Look, we have a problem
outside.

04:56.504 --> 04:58.465
- Okay.
- An unhoused gentleman

04:58.506 --> 04:59.799
who's facing some challenges

04:59.841 --> 05:02.635
has created
an untenable environment.

05:02.677 --> 05:04.346
- I don't--I don't follow.
What are you saying?

05:04.387 --> 05:06.890
- There's a crazy
homeless guy out front.

05:06.931 --> 05:08.683
He's scaring our patients.
I need him gone.

05:08.725 --> 05:10.643
- Well, that was a touching
and heartfelt alternate way

05:10.685 --> 05:11.895
of putting that.
Thank you.

05:11.936 --> 05:13.438
- I'm suggesting
you provide him

05:13.480 --> 05:15.690
with appropriate care
and services.

05:15.732 --> 05:16.941
- That is far away
from our entrance.

05:16.983 --> 05:19.152
- [sighs] Thank you, Ignatius.
- You got it.

05:19.194 --> 05:21.738
- Do not go inside!

05:21.780 --> 05:24.157
Yes. Yes.

05:24.199 --> 05:25.158
Come out.

05:25.200 --> 05:28.328
Get away from them.

05:28.370 --> 05:30.038
Stop. Stop.

05:30.080 --> 05:31.289
They will kill you!

05:31.331 --> 05:32.832
- Hey, there. Hey.

05:32.874 --> 05:34.334
Got a little something here
that might brighten your day.

05:34.376 --> 05:37.003
- Evil. Evil people.

05:37.045 --> 05:38.546
- Okay. Sure. Sure.

05:38.588 --> 05:40.090
- You're one of them.

05:40.131 --> 05:44.386
- Actually, I'm just a guy
with some socks.

05:45.428 --> 05:48.014
Yeah, yeah.

05:48.973 --> 05:51.142
Want a pair?

05:51.184 --> 05:53.728
Yeah. Go ahead. Take a pair.
It's cold out here.

05:54.562 --> 05:57.065
Yeah, you're good. Yeah.

05:57.107 --> 05:58.483
I got a whole bag
full of socks here.

05:58.525 --> 06:00.318
I got sweaters.

06:00.360 --> 06:01.820
What you say
you and I take this

06:01.861 --> 06:03.029
wherever you're camping out

06:03.071 --> 06:04.906
and we stash
the whole bag there?

06:06.574 --> 06:08.952
- I got a place
just over there.

06:10.537 --> 06:12.247
- Oh, over here under
the scaffolding?

06:12.288 --> 06:13.957
Yeah. I've seen people there.

06:13.998 --> 06:16.042
- No.

06:16.084 --> 06:17.502
No.

06:17.544 --> 06:19.212
<i>[soft music]</i>

06:19.254 --> 06:20.380
Penthouse.

06:20.422 --> 06:24.426
<i>* *</i>

06:24.467 --> 06:26.052
- Penthouse?

06:26.094 --> 06:27.887
<i>* *</i>

06:27.929 --> 06:29.389
Right on.

06:29.431 --> 06:30.557
<i>* *</i>

06:30.598 --> 06:33.518
<i>[jazzy percussive music]</i>

06:33.560 --> 06:40.692
<i>* *</i>

08:33.096 --> 08:35.724
<i>[soft music]</i>

08:35.765 --> 08:37.600
- Oh, that is quite
the decision.

08:37.642 --> 08:39.019
- Tell me about it.
- Right.

08:39.060 --> 08:41.271
So you can either hang out
with a bunch of AARP guys

08:41.312 --> 08:44.357
at a literal fish show,
or you can hook up

08:44.399 --> 08:47.902
with a beautiful, available,
interested woman.

08:47.944 --> 08:49.612
Yeah.
I can see why you're torn.

08:49.654 --> 08:50.780
- It's not that easy,
all right?

08:50.822 --> 08:52.532
All I've ever wanted
was my family back.

08:52.574 --> 08:53.908
And now that I have it--

08:53.950 --> 08:56.286
- Young woman found
down in Morandi Park.

08:56.327 --> 08:57.537
Unresponsive.

08:57.579 --> 08:59.330
Respirations
and heart rate slow.

08:59.372 --> 09:00.498
- Vanessa.

09:00.540 --> 09:02.167
Vanessa?

09:02.208 --> 09:04.044
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:04.085 --> 09:05.837
Pupils are pinpoint,
nonreactive.

09:05.879 --> 09:07.213
- Narcotics overdose.

09:07.255 --> 09:08.089
- I need a second IV.

09:08.131 --> 09:10.300
- O-2 sats are low.
- On it.

09:10.342 --> 09:12.218
- Saturation 88%.

09:12.260 --> 09:14.387
- I need an intubation tray
with a seven.

09:14.429 --> 09:16.264
<i>* *</i>

09:16.306 --> 09:18.224
- Pushing Narcan.

09:18.266 --> 09:21.227
[machinery beeping]

09:21.269 --> 09:28.193
<i>* *</i>

09:30.737 --> 09:33.448
[no audible dialogue]

09:33.490 --> 09:40.622
<i>* *</i>

09:48.171 --> 09:48.338
.

09:48.380 --> 09:48.838
- Quick pop quiz.

09:49.714 --> 09:51.132
This is from a 65-year-old man

09:51.174 --> 09:52.676
who is hypertensive
and unconscious.

09:52.717 --> 09:54.594
Do you shock this rhythm?

09:54.636 --> 09:56.554
- No.

09:56.596 --> 09:57.639
- Yes.

09:57.681 --> 09:58.890
All right.

09:58.932 --> 10:00.266
So you just flip through
these four screens,

10:00.308 --> 10:02.060
and then you pull down
this tab right here.

10:02.102 --> 10:04.479
And, oh, the M key
does not work.

10:04.521 --> 10:07.982
So we just use a little "rn"
right next to each other.

10:08.024 --> 10:10.235
- Someone's gotta build
a better system.

10:10.276 --> 10:11.486
- Oh.
What if that's someone is you?

10:11.528 --> 10:13.405
When you approach a patient
about hospice,

10:13.446 --> 10:15.156
you don't talk
about end-of-life care.

10:15.198 --> 10:18.034
You just talk about life care.

10:18.076 --> 10:19.953
This is just
the next stage of it.

10:19.994 --> 10:21.955
[machinery beeping]

10:21.996 --> 10:23.456
- It's Duane Roberts.
- All right.

10:23.498 --> 10:24.708
This is it.

10:24.749 --> 10:26.751
You're up.

10:26.793 --> 10:28.712
- [gasping]

10:28.753 --> 10:30.630
- BP 60 over 49.

10:30.672 --> 10:31.715
- Absent breath sounds
on the left.

10:31.756 --> 10:33.008
- Left heart's straining EKG.

10:33.049 --> 10:35.343
- Tension pneumo.
Need a left-sided chest tube.

10:35.385 --> 10:38.346
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

10:38.388 --> 10:40.306
<i>* *</i>

10:40.348 --> 10:41.433
- VAN runs under the rib.

10:41.474 --> 10:48.440
<i>* *</i>

10:48.481 --> 10:52.944
- BP rising.

10:52.986 --> 10:54.029
- Sats normalizing.

10:54.070 --> 10:55.655
- [sighs] It worked.

10:55.697 --> 10:57.574
- That's good work.

10:57.615 --> 11:01.578
Decision, coordination,
execution, all excellent.

11:01.619 --> 11:02.912
<i>[tense music]</i>

11:02.954 --> 11:06.374
- Mika, you okay?

11:06.416 --> 11:11.796
<i>* *</i>

12:29.666 --> 12:31.626
- It used to be cleaner.

12:31.668 --> 12:32.794
- Oh, no, no.

12:32.836 --> 12:35.296
This is, uh--this is amazing.

12:35.338 --> 12:36.923
Wow.

12:38.174 --> 12:40.802
Look at this place.

12:40.844 --> 12:42.804
Look at that view.

12:42.846 --> 12:44.848
Oh, someone's a gamer, huh?

12:46.349 --> 12:47.308
- Uh, coder.

12:47.350 --> 12:48.935
Bitcoin.

12:48.977 --> 12:50.812
- Cooler. [chuckles]

12:50.854 --> 12:53.565
- Do you want one?

12:53.606 --> 12:55.525
- Yeah. Yeah. Thank you.

12:55.567 --> 12:56.943
I'll take one of those.

12:56.985 --> 12:58.945
Cheers.

12:58.987 --> 13:02.407
So, hey, just curious.

13:02.449 --> 13:04.909
Why did you start hanging out
in front of New Amsterdam?

13:06.870 --> 13:08.204
- I'm warning people.

13:08.246 --> 13:09.497
- Warning people about what?

13:09.539 --> 13:10.957
- Bad things happen
in that place.

13:10.999 --> 13:12.584
They're evil. They hurt people.

13:12.625 --> 13:17.088
They do experiments
on young children.

13:17.130 --> 13:19.841
They use lightning,
and they rip out their brains.

13:19.883 --> 13:21.926
They tie them down with rubber.

13:21.968 --> 13:23.470
And it's tight.

13:23.511 --> 13:25.472
No! It burns.

13:25.513 --> 13:26.848
And they zap.

13:26.890 --> 13:28.516
They zap and zap and zap.

13:28.558 --> 13:29.684
They...

13:29.726 --> 13:33.480
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

13:33.521 --> 13:35.815
I'm saving those kids.

13:35.857 --> 13:37.609
- Tied down with rubber?

13:37.650 --> 13:38.693
Lightning?

13:38.735 --> 13:40.528
- Don't--don't try to deny it.

13:40.570 --> 13:42.030
- No, no, I'm not.
That--that is how they

13:42.072 --> 13:45.075
used to do electroshock therapy
40 years ago.

13:46.368 --> 13:47.535
Harlan, when you were a kid,

13:47.577 --> 13:49.704
were you a patient
at New Amsterdam?

13:49.746 --> 13:52.499
- Oh...[grunts]

13:52.540 --> 13:59.422
<i>* *</i>

14:03.843 --> 14:06.471
- Hey, how you doing?

14:07.597 --> 14:10.350
- [groans]
How does it freaking look?

14:10.392 --> 14:13.103
[groans]
- It's the Narcan.

14:13.144 --> 14:14.813
You're in withdrawal
from the heroin.

14:14.854 --> 14:18.108
- Well, it feels like ants
are crawling out of my body.

14:18.149 --> 14:19.901
So--oh, Jesus.

14:19.943 --> 14:21.194
- All right. Okay.

14:21.236 --> 14:22.612
We're gonna get you
through this.

14:22.654 --> 14:24.406
- Stop. Get off.
- What?

14:24.447 --> 14:26.032
- Stop gloating, all right?
- I'm not gloating.

14:26.074 --> 14:27.409
- Please just leave.
- Okay, you really--

14:27.450 --> 14:29.202
Ugh. Jesus.

14:32.205 --> 14:33.748
All right.
You know what, Vanessa?

14:33.790 --> 14:35.083
You tried to kill yourself.

14:35.125 --> 14:36.334
Whether you realize it or not,

14:36.376 --> 14:37.502
that is what you tried to do.

14:37.544 --> 14:39.671
And I'm gonna be here for you,
okay?

14:42.215 --> 14:44.175
- Yeah. Well, you know what?

14:44.217 --> 14:45.760
Being nice to me now
is not gonna change the fact

14:45.802 --> 14:47.721
that Mom died hating you.

14:52.976 --> 14:55.437
- That's not true.

14:55.478 --> 14:56.896
- Yes, it is.

14:56.938 --> 14:58.440
Yeah, it is, actually.

14:58.481 --> 15:02.068
Thanks to me, she wrote you
a letter a few years ago,

15:02.110 --> 15:03.820
an apology, you know,

15:03.862 --> 15:06.114
for being
such a terrible mother.

15:06.156 --> 15:08.158
I threw it away.

15:16.833 --> 15:20.462
- Why would you do that?

15:20.503 --> 15:21.588
Answer me.

15:21.629 --> 15:23.131
Why would you do that?

15:23.173 --> 15:25.342
- Because you didn't deserve
that, Lauren!

15:25.383 --> 15:26.509
God, she was so vulnerable

15:26.551 --> 15:28.470
when she came to me
with that letter.

15:28.511 --> 15:30.305
She was, like, crying
and asking me

15:30.347 --> 15:32.349
if I thought you'd ever
forgive her.

15:32.390 --> 15:34.017
She thought
you threw it in her face.

15:34.059 --> 15:35.310
So yes, Lauren. Yes.

15:35.352 --> 15:38.104
I'm pretty sure
she died hating you.

15:38.146 --> 15:39.314
- You know what?

15:39.356 --> 15:40.315
You really are pathetic,
aren't you?

15:40.357 --> 15:41.733
- And there she is. You see,

15:41.775 --> 15:42.984
this is who you really are.

15:43.026 --> 15:44.569
- How many times
do I have to tell you?

15:44.611 --> 15:46.821
I'm done with it!
- Selfish bitch!

15:46.863 --> 15:48.114
- I'm done with being there!
- I can't stand

15:48.156 --> 15:49.657
the condescending bitch
you've become.

15:49.699 --> 15:52.619
[thuds]
- Vanessa? Vanessa? Vanessa?

15:52.660 --> 15:54.662
I need help in here!

15:54.704 --> 15:55.997
Okay, okay, okay.

15:56.039 --> 15:57.582
Okay, okay. Okay.

16:02.796 --> 16:03.171
.

16:03.213 --> 16:04.172
- Chest, it hurts.
- What do you got?

16:05.256 --> 16:07.092
- Hypertensive,
diaphoretic, tachy.

16:07.133 --> 16:08.843
Probably narcotic withdrawal.

16:08.885 --> 16:10.679
- My chest.
- Vanessa, I know it hurts,

16:10.720 --> 16:12.222
but we need you to stay still,
okay?

16:12.263 --> 16:14.224
Start an Esmolol drip.

16:14.265 --> 16:16.768
- TOX screen?
- The usual polypharmacy.

16:16.810 --> 16:19.312
Oxy, meth, cocaine,
marijuana, you name it.

16:19.354 --> 16:20.730
- Was she acting erratically?

16:20.772 --> 16:24.859
- She was outta control,
screaming the most hateful--

16:24.901 --> 16:26.194
an adrenergic storm.

16:26.236 --> 16:28.071
- From acute cocaine toxicity.

16:28.113 --> 16:29.989
Her coronary artery
is spasming.

16:30.031 --> 16:31.574
- I didn't see it. I--

16:31.616 --> 16:33.410
-We gotta get her
to a cath lab now.

16:33.451 --> 16:34.661
- The clues
were right in front of me,

16:34.703 --> 16:35.912
but why didn't I see it?

16:35.954 --> 16:37.997
- With family, we never see it.

16:38.039 --> 16:40.250
Let's go.

16:40.291 --> 16:41.751
Straight. Straight. This way.

16:41.793 --> 16:44.254
<i>* *</i>

16:46.965 --> 16:48.091
- Hey.

16:48.133 --> 16:50.093
- Hey.
- You okay?

16:50.135 --> 16:52.262
- Uh, yeah,
it was just allergies.

16:52.303 --> 16:56.224
- It didn't look
like allergies.

16:56.266 --> 16:57.767
Looked like a panic attack.

16:57.809 --> 16:59.853
- Oh, no. Not at all.

16:59.894 --> 17:01.896
I mean, I've been here a month,
and Elliot's code

17:01.938 --> 17:03.398
isn't one of the top ten
most intense things

17:03.440 --> 17:05.066
that have happened all week.

17:05.108 --> 17:06.735
- Who's Elliot?

17:06.776 --> 17:08.653
- The--the patient.
The code we just ran.

17:10.071 --> 17:12.741
- No, Mika.
That was Duane.

17:13.992 --> 17:15.952
Who's Elliot?

17:15.994 --> 17:17.495
- Um...

17:21.166 --> 17:24.127
My first patient here.

17:24.169 --> 17:25.962
You never forget your first,
right?

17:26.004 --> 17:27.380
- No.

17:27.422 --> 17:29.424
Especially if they die.

17:34.346 --> 17:36.222
- How did you know that?

17:36.264 --> 17:39.351
- 'Cause I've stood
where you're standing.

17:39.392 --> 17:42.187
Patients die, Mika,
no matter what you do,

17:42.228 --> 17:43.521
no matter how good you are,

17:43.563 --> 17:46.191
and I've been watching you
on the floor.

17:46.232 --> 17:48.985
You're a really good doctor.

17:49.027 --> 17:52.864
- No. [sighs]

17:52.906 --> 17:54.491
I'm an excellent doctor.

17:54.532 --> 17:56.785
Elliot had a triple A
that ruptured.

17:56.826 --> 17:58.703
That's one of the hardest
procedures we do,

17:58.745 --> 18:01.331
and I ran that code flawlessly.

18:07.379 --> 18:09.839
And then I went home
for the night,

18:09.881 --> 18:11.841
and he died

18:11.883 --> 18:14.511
while I was watching
a reality cooking show

18:14.552 --> 18:16.680
and eating a takeaway salad.

18:18.973 --> 18:21.643
I could have saved him.

18:21.685 --> 18:24.270
He was my patient,
and I left him to die.

18:29.818 --> 18:34.322
- They experimented on me
with lightning.

18:36.074 --> 18:37.200
It hurt.

18:37.242 --> 18:39.828
- Yeah, I bet.

18:39.869 --> 18:41.538
Yeah, a lot of hospitals
back then used

18:41.579 --> 18:44.541
a very crude version
of electroshock,

18:44.582 --> 18:47.002
and they way overmedicated.

18:47.043 --> 18:48.586
Just so many pills.

18:48.628 --> 18:50.046
You could barely even move.

18:50.088 --> 18:51.423
- [exhales shakily]

18:54.592 --> 18:56.761
It's like being in a cage.

18:58.596 --> 19:00.765
A cage you can't see.

19:05.937 --> 19:07.939
- You know, Harlan,

19:07.981 --> 19:10.066
we don't do that anymore.

19:10.108 --> 19:12.277
- [scoffs]
- No, we don't.

19:12.318 --> 19:13.737
And I have helped
schizophrenics

19:13.778 --> 19:16.990
without pills, without shocks.

19:17.032 --> 19:18.658
None of it.

19:18.700 --> 19:19.492
- Really?

19:19.534 --> 19:21.911
- Yeah, really.

19:21.953 --> 19:24.706
If you come with me
to my office today,

19:24.748 --> 19:26.833
I will get you
back on your feet.

19:26.875 --> 19:30.128
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

19:30.170 --> 19:32.255
- [grunts]

19:32.297 --> 19:33.298
It doesn't believe you.

19:33.340 --> 19:34.591
- The voice?

19:34.632 --> 19:36.092
- Mm...
- Yeah. That's okay.

19:36.134 --> 19:37.510
That's okay. That's okay.

19:37.552 --> 19:40.805
But all you have to do
is let me try,

19:40.847 --> 19:42.891
and you will see
that I can help you.

19:42.932 --> 19:44.267
I mean, Harlan, look
at what you've accomplished.

19:44.309 --> 19:45.643
Look at this.

19:45.685 --> 19:47.520
You were doing really well
for a very long time.

19:47.562 --> 19:48.938
- Stop talking.

19:48.980 --> 19:50.940
- Look, going to the hospital,
that's new, right?

19:50.982 --> 19:52.817
- Shut up!

19:52.859 --> 19:54.319
<i>* *</i>

19:54.361 --> 19:55.570
- Did something happen
recently?

19:55.612 --> 19:56.571
Something--
- Get out.

19:56.613 --> 19:58.448
Get outta here now!

19:58.490 --> 20:00.241
Get outta here right now.
- Okay.

20:00.283 --> 20:01.201
- No hospitals!

20:01.242 --> 20:02.452
No doctors!

20:02.494 --> 20:03.661
No, no, no!

20:03.703 --> 20:04.496
No!

20:04.537 --> 20:11.670
<i>* *</i>

22:53.790 --> 22:53.998
.

22:54.040 --> 22:54.499
<i>[somber music]</i>

22:57.002 --> 23:03.925
<i>* *</i>

23:45.800 --> 23:49.679
- Morandi Park.

23:49.721 --> 23:51.264
- I don't--

23:51.306 --> 23:54.351
- Vanessa lives
on the Upper West Side.

23:54.392 --> 23:57.979
So do all of her friends.

23:58.021 --> 24:02.275
Yet she OD'd in Morandi Park...

24:02.317 --> 24:05.195
directly across the street
from this hospital.

24:05.236 --> 24:10.617
<i>* *</i>

24:10.658 --> 24:13.203
She knew exactly
where they'd bring her.

24:13.244 --> 24:17.040
<i>* *</i>

24:17.082 --> 24:19.709
She knew that I'd be the one
to see her like this.

24:19.751 --> 24:23.672
<i>* *</i>

24:23.713 --> 24:25.632
She chose this.

24:25.674 --> 24:29.302
<i>* *</i>

24:29.344 --> 24:31.513
That's how much she hates me.

24:31.554 --> 24:32.764
- Well, she was coked
out of her mind.

24:32.806 --> 24:35.392
- It wasn't the coke.

24:35.433 --> 24:37.644
She meant what she said,
every last word of it.

24:37.686 --> 24:39.396
She meant it.

24:39.437 --> 24:41.898
<i>* *</i>

24:41.940 --> 24:44.275
And why shouldn't she hate me?

24:44.317 --> 24:47.070
<i>* *</i>

24:47.112 --> 24:48.154
I left her.

24:48.196 --> 24:49.906
- Lauren...

24:52.659 --> 24:54.869
- You wanna know
the worst part?

24:56.579 --> 25:00.208
If she never woke up,

25:00.250 --> 25:03.253
I think a part of me
would be relieved.

25:03.294 --> 25:09.426
<i>* *</i>

25:09.467 --> 25:12.429
Why didn't I help her?

25:12.470 --> 25:14.597
[sobbing]

25:14.639 --> 25:18.852
- You know why
better than anyone.

25:18.893 --> 25:20.645
An addict has to want help.

25:20.687 --> 25:22.522
- I have to try.
I have to try.

25:22.564 --> 25:24.816
I can't--I can't just stand by
and do nothing.

25:24.858 --> 25:26.568
- No, you--
- No, Floyd, I'm not just gonna

25:26.609 --> 25:29.320
walk away
and just watch her die.

25:31.281 --> 25:33.450
This time I'm staying.

25:33.491 --> 25:38.997
<i>* *</i>

25:42.792 --> 25:43.960
- Get out.

25:44.002 --> 25:45.128
Don't you spy on me.
- I'm not.

25:45.170 --> 25:46.796
- Don't you spy.
- 48 floors.

25:46.838 --> 25:48.048
It just--it takes a minute.

25:48.089 --> 25:51.217
- Damn thing. Hurry up.
Hurry up.

25:51.259 --> 25:53.762
<i>[soft music]</i>

25:53.803 --> 25:56.473
- Hey, the protein shakes,
you like 'em?

25:56.514 --> 25:57.640
They good?

25:57.682 --> 25:59.351
<i>* *</i>

25:59.392 --> 26:00.477
- Yeah.

26:00.518 --> 26:02.145
<i>* *</i>

26:02.187 --> 26:03.355
- Did you start drinking them

26:03.396 --> 26:04.939
right before
you started warning people

26:04.981 --> 26:06.191
out in front of the hospital?

26:06.232 --> 26:08.234
<i>* *</i>

26:08.276 --> 26:09.486
- What?

26:09.527 --> 26:11.321
<i>* *</i>

26:15.909 --> 26:19.371
- The M key doesn't work.
Remember?

26:19.412 --> 26:21.456
Gotta just use "rn."

26:21.498 --> 26:22.749
- Thanks.

26:24.668 --> 26:26.753
- Mika, you left your patient
'cause your shift was over.

26:26.795 --> 26:28.421
- [sighs]

26:28.463 --> 26:30.173
Can we not talk about this?

26:30.215 --> 26:32.884
- Well, I can't let you
see patients until we do.

26:36.304 --> 26:37.764
- Fine.

26:40.892 --> 26:43.395
I could have stayed.

26:43.436 --> 26:45.355
I chose to leave.

26:45.397 --> 26:49.025
- When you're not on call,
do you ever sleep here?

26:49.067 --> 26:50.110
- We all grab naps sometimes.

26:50.151 --> 26:52.654
- That's not what I meant.

26:52.696 --> 26:53.905
How often do you go home?

26:53.947 --> 26:56.741
- It depends.

26:56.783 --> 26:59.119
- Mika, I'm just asking you,

26:59.160 --> 27:00.954
when was the last time
that you got

27:00.995 --> 27:04.749
a full night's sleep
in your own bed?

27:09.879 --> 27:13.341
- [sighs]

27:13.383 --> 27:15.468
The night Elliot died.

27:15.510 --> 27:18.888
<i>[solemn music]</i>

27:18.930 --> 27:21.266
- That was over a month ago.

27:21.307 --> 27:22.600
<i>* *</i>

27:22.642 --> 27:25.478
Mika, you have to go home.

27:25.520 --> 27:27.605
It's not a request.

27:27.647 --> 27:30.066
- I don't think you're allowed
to dictate where I sleep,

27:30.108 --> 27:32.068
and my performance
isn't a problem.

27:32.110 --> 27:35.113
So thank you for your concern,
truly.

27:35.155 --> 27:38.283
But I'm not going anywhere.

27:38.324 --> 27:45.248
<i>* *</i>

27:56.051 --> 27:57.802
- You want to take the job.

27:58.970 --> 28:00.096
- I have to.

28:00.138 --> 28:01.598
It's too important.

28:01.639 --> 28:04.142
I won't leave you in the lurch.

28:04.184 --> 28:05.560
I'll help with the transition.

28:05.602 --> 28:08.063
I will handle the interviews
for my replacement.

28:09.064 --> 28:12.150
- Can we talk alone?

28:16.654 --> 28:18.198
- I'll be right outside.

30:09.768 --> 30:12.729
<i>[soft music]</i>

30:12.771 --> 30:18.401
<i>* *</i>

30:22.822 --> 30:23.198
.

30:23.239 --> 30:24.032
- Hey, hey.
I have good news.

30:25.408 --> 30:27.327
- You dealt with the homeless--
unhoused gentleman?

30:27.369 --> 30:28.828
- Yes. His name is Harlan,

30:28.870 --> 30:30.580
and I did help him indeed.

30:30.622 --> 30:33.792
It turns out the problem
was protein shakes.

30:33.833 --> 30:36.086
- It didn't look like
the problem was protein shakes.

30:36.127 --> 30:37.128
- Well, upon further
inspection,

30:37.170 --> 30:38.421
they were all he was eating,

30:38.463 --> 30:41.091
which led to a niacin
deficiency, AKA pellagra,

30:41.132 --> 30:42.967
which I then treated
with a multivitamin.

30:43.009 --> 30:44.469
- So he wasn't schizophrenic,

30:44.511 --> 30:46.137
he just needed
Flintstone pills?

30:46.179 --> 30:47.722
- He is still schizophrenic,

30:47.764 --> 30:50.183
just minus the aggressive
behavior, the irritability,

30:50.225 --> 30:51.351
and the angry voices
in his head.

30:51.393 --> 30:52.894
That was all the pellagra.

30:52.936 --> 30:55.397
- As long as sanity has
prevailed at our front door,

30:55.438 --> 30:56.981
I'm happy.
- Yeah.

30:57.023 --> 30:58.441
Yeah.
Well, you know, about that.

30:58.483 --> 31:00.235
- Do you get your vitamins?

31:00.276 --> 31:01.861
There's 13 essential ones.

31:01.903 --> 31:03.988
They're good for your bones,
your immune system.

31:04.030 --> 31:05.198
This will save your life.

31:05.240 --> 31:07.158
- I told you to clear
the front door.

31:07.200 --> 31:09.119
- No. No, you told me to help.

31:09.160 --> 31:10.829
- Hey, Iggy!
- And I did.

31:10.870 --> 31:12.288
- Hey!
- Hey, doing great.

31:12.330 --> 31:14.207
- Excuse me.
Do you get your vitamins?

31:14.249 --> 31:15.959
Vitamins are really good
for you.

31:16.001 --> 31:18.044
- [sighs]

31:22.757 --> 31:23.800
- You're still here.

31:25.051 --> 31:26.136
- Dr. Goodwin.

31:26.177 --> 31:27.554
- You gotta go.

31:29.014 --> 31:31.057
Stay, and you're a bad doctor.

31:33.351 --> 31:35.228
- Are you asking me
to care less?

31:35.270 --> 31:38.106
- No. If anything,
I'm asking you to care more.

31:39.733 --> 31:42.360
The hardest part of caring
is the part you're not doing.

31:42.402 --> 31:45.196
Letting go.
- Giving up is not caring.

31:46.906 --> 31:49.367
- Elliot's gone.

31:49.409 --> 31:51.202
If you worked
1,000 hours straight,

31:51.244 --> 31:52.579
it wouldn't bring him back.

31:52.620 --> 31:54.122
You can't undo it.
- Stop.

31:54.164 --> 31:57.292
- Sometimes people go,

31:57.334 --> 31:58.918
and wanting them to stay,

31:58.960 --> 32:01.004
fighting, clinging,

32:01.046 --> 32:03.256
that's for you.

32:03.298 --> 32:04.924
<i>[soft music]</i>

32:04.966 --> 32:06.301
And you going home,

32:06.343 --> 32:08.803
that's for the person
who needs you next.

32:08.845 --> 32:15.769
<i>* *</i>

32:17.937 --> 32:19.397
Can I walk you out?

32:19.439 --> 32:20.899
- [inhales shakily]

32:20.940 --> 32:22.025
Yeah.

32:22.067 --> 32:25.236
<i>* *</i>

32:31.951 --> 32:33.203
- Is she--

32:33.244 --> 32:35.747
- Vanessa's awake,

32:35.789 --> 32:37.457
and she's asking for you.

32:37.499 --> 32:39.209
- [sighs]

32:40.835 --> 32:42.712
- You don't have to go.

32:42.754 --> 32:45.340
Don't keep doing this
to yourself.

32:46.800 --> 32:49.302
- She's family.

32:49.344 --> 32:51.429
You don't turn your back
on that.

32:51.471 --> 32:54.474
- Well, I thought that too.

32:54.516 --> 32:58.061
With my dad when I was trying
to get into his life,

32:58.103 --> 33:01.439
I made so many excuses for him.

33:01.481 --> 33:05.735
I said I wasn't gonna be
the one who turned away,

33:05.777 --> 33:08.321
but my friend told me
that was crap.

33:10.073 --> 33:11.658
- It's not the same.

33:11.700 --> 33:17.205
- You said that change won't
happen unless you demand it.

33:18.456 --> 33:22.210
- But what if it doesn't?

33:22.252 --> 33:25.714
What if she needs me,
and I'm not there?

33:25.755 --> 33:27.966
<i>[somber music]</i>

33:28.008 --> 33:29.968
What if she dies?

33:30.010 --> 33:32.220
<i>* *</i>

33:32.262 --> 33:34.973
I don't know how to help her.

33:35.015 --> 33:38.309
<i>* *</i>

33:38.351 --> 33:40.311
[crying] I don't know how--

33:40.353 --> 33:41.604
I don't know how to help her.

33:41.646 --> 33:43.898
- Yes, you do. Yes, you do.

33:43.940 --> 33:47.068
You've already done it once
when you were 18.

33:47.110 --> 33:48.737
- No.

33:48.778 --> 33:50.655
<i>* *</i>

33:50.697 --> 33:52.032
That was selfish.

33:52.073 --> 33:53.658
You know, me leaving her,

33:53.700 --> 33:55.827
that put that needle
in her arm.

33:55.869 --> 33:57.412
- Listen.

33:57.454 --> 34:00.832
If you hadn't left,
you'd be in a bed next to her.

34:00.874 --> 34:02.709
All right?
She has someone alive

34:02.751 --> 34:07.839
to help her
because you left, right?

34:07.881 --> 34:10.008
<i>* *</i>

34:10.050 --> 34:14.346
You spent most of your life
wishing you can change things.

34:14.387 --> 34:16.139
But you know what?

34:16.181 --> 34:18.266
<i>* *</i>

34:18.308 --> 34:20.769
It wasn't the worst thing
you ever did.

34:20.810 --> 34:23.063
It was the best.

34:23.104 --> 34:27.025
And I think Vanessa needs you
to do it again.

34:27.067 --> 34:34.032
<i>* *</i>

34:34.074 --> 34:36.951
[machines beeping]

34:47.253 --> 34:49.881
- She's not coming?

34:49.923 --> 34:51.007
- No.

34:53.176 --> 34:54.969
But she wanted me
to give you this.

34:58.682 --> 35:00.725
That's where she'll be.

35:11.069 --> 35:13.029
- Hey, Pops.
Give me a minute to change,

35:13.071 --> 35:16.282
and we can hit that tri--

35:17.826 --> 35:19.411
What's happening?

35:19.452 --> 35:21.538
- I'm moving out.

35:23.289 --> 35:25.208
- Okay. If you're...

35:25.250 --> 35:26.459
feeling anxious
about something,

35:26.501 --> 35:28.670
we can work through it.
- Son, I'm good.

35:30.130 --> 35:31.297
Have a seat.

35:32.298 --> 35:35.385
[siren wailing in distance]

35:38.680 --> 35:41.433
This may be hard
for you to hear,

35:41.474 --> 35:43.184
but I read all your texts.

35:43.226 --> 35:44.602
- Pops!
- Easy.

35:44.644 --> 35:46.438
It was an accident.

35:46.479 --> 35:48.148
I was checking out vendors
for the expo.

35:48.189 --> 35:50.275
And when I closed the browser,

35:50.316 --> 35:53.278
your message app
was all over the screen.

35:53.319 --> 35:55.864
The thread
with this Gabrielle girl.

35:56.531 --> 35:58.450
I tried not to look,
but those pictures--

35:58.491 --> 35:59.534
- Oh, my God.

35:59.576 --> 36:01.286
- Calm down. I didn't linger,

36:01.327 --> 36:02.787
but I got enough to know

36:02.829 --> 36:05.373
that you are about to make
the wrong call.

36:05.415 --> 36:07.042
- Oh, no, no, no, no.

36:07.083 --> 36:11.254
Pops, look,
you are not in the way.

36:11.296 --> 36:13.965
This isn't pity.

36:14.007 --> 36:15.967
I want to pick you.

36:16.009 --> 36:17.385
- I don't know
if I got the right

36:17.427 --> 36:21.973
to give you fatherly advice,
but if I did,

36:22.015 --> 36:24.017
I'd say the most important
thing I've learned

36:24.059 --> 36:26.811
is you go for the girl.

36:34.069 --> 36:35.862
- No, Pops. Pops, wait.

36:35.904 --> 36:37.280
Just...

36:37.322 --> 36:40.283
<i>[soft music]</i>

36:40.325 --> 36:42.577
<i>* *</i>

36:42.619 --> 36:46.873
I'm afraid
I won't see you again.

36:46.915 --> 36:52.921
- Son, the first time I left,
that was selfish.

36:52.962 --> 36:57.175
This time,
I'm doing it for you.

36:57.217 --> 37:03.890
<i>* *</i>

37:03.932 --> 37:06.184
- Hello.

37:06.226 --> 37:08.269
So is anybody in the mood

37:08.311 --> 37:11.856
for a sweeping
romantic gesture?

37:11.898 --> 37:16.361
This Cab is both robust
and impertinent,

37:16.403 --> 37:18.029
much like myself.

37:18.071 --> 37:19.781
Iggy in a bottle.

37:23.702 --> 37:25.245
- [chuckles quietly]
- Hey.

37:25.286 --> 37:26.746
Hey.
- Hey.

37:26.788 --> 37:28.623
- So I know last night
was a lot,

37:28.665 --> 37:32.085
um, but it was wonderful.

37:32.127 --> 37:34.879
Maybe things haven't changed
that much.

37:34.921 --> 37:37.841
- Yeah, our good parts
are still good.

37:39.467 --> 37:42.262
But what's it say
about the bad parts?

37:42.303 --> 37:44.681
- I don't know.

37:44.723 --> 37:47.392
You know, we'll find out.

37:47.434 --> 37:49.561
Maybe--maybe they're better.

37:51.104 --> 37:53.523
- Maybe's not an answer.

37:54.107 --> 37:58.069
We can't just blindly hope
that our problems

37:58.111 --> 37:59.654
have magically solved
themselves.

37:59.696 --> 38:00.989
- I don't think that, Martin.

38:01.031 --> 38:03.783
I'm not--I'm not waiting

38:03.825 --> 38:05.410
for them to magically
solve themselves.

38:05.452 --> 38:07.871
I'm--I'm working at changing.

38:07.912 --> 38:09.664
I have changed.
You've seen it.

38:09.706 --> 38:11.332
- Mm-hmm.
- And I'm not just talking

38:11.374 --> 38:12.584
about the physical,
the outside.

38:12.625 --> 38:13.585
You know,
I'm talking about inside.

38:13.626 --> 38:15.086
I feel different.

38:15.128 --> 38:16.421
I'm different.

38:16.463 --> 38:19.466
- Iggy, so am I.

38:25.096 --> 38:27.349
<i>[solemn music]</i>

